claim.claim-text:
1. A nonvolatile semiconductor memory comprising:
a first and a second active area configured to extend in the column direction in parallel;
an element isolating region configured to electrically separate the first and the second active area;
a plurality of word lines configured to extend in the row direction and comprise respective main parts and respective ends;
a plurality of memory cell transistors configured to be disposed on intersections between the respective main parts of the plurality of word lines and the second active area; wherein each memory cell transistor comprises a gate insulating film, a floating gate electrode, an inter-gate insulating film, and a control gate electrode, so as to comprise a memory cell array;
a short-circuit region configured to electrically short circuit the ends of the plurality of word lines; and
a trench configured to separate the ends from the main parts of the plurality of word lines.

11. A fabrication method for a nonvolatile semiconductor memory comprising: a first and a second active area configured to extend in parallel in the column direction; an element isolating region configured to electrically separate the first and the second active area; a plurality of word lines, which extend in the row direction and have respective main parts and respective ends; a plurality of memory cell transistors configured to be disposed on intersections between the respective main parts of the plurality of word lines and the second active area, where each memory cell transistor comprises a gate insulating film, a floating gate electrode, an inter-gate insulating film, and a control gate electrode, so as to comprise a memory cell array; a short-circuit region configured to electrically short circuit the ends of the plurality of word lines; and a trench configured to separate the ends from the main parts of the plurality of word lines; said fabrication method comprising:
fabricating a stacked layer structure comprising a stacked nitride film, a metallic salicide film, the control gate electrode, the inter-gate insulating film, and the floating gate electrode, and short circuiting the ends of the plurality of word lines in the short-circuit region;
coating a resist across the entire surface of an element region on a semiconductor substrate, and patterning the trench;
etching the nitride film, the metallic salicide film, and the control gate electrode using the resist as a mask, and forming an aperture of the trench; and
removing the resist.
